BEGIN:VEVENT
X-SOURCE:IU Asian Culture Center
DTSTART:20260414T210000Z
DTEND:20260414T220000Z
LOCATION:Asian Culture Center (807 E 10th street\, Bloomington\, IN)
SUMMARY:ACC Book Club features "To Save and Destroy" by Viet Nguyen
DESCRIPTION:This is our last book discussion meeting. What does it mean t
 o be&#160\;an "other"? How can writing shift the boundaries between insid
 er and outsider for both author and audience? All are welcome to join the
  ACC in discussing these questions over pizza. We will discuss the last t
 wo essays of Viet Thanh Nguyen's essay collection&#160\;To Save and to De
 stroy: Writing as an Other. Digital copies of the eBook are&#160\;freely 
 available to access through IU Libraries&#160\;  &#160\;For more informat
 ion\, please reach out to ACC volunteer and book club moderator Cheryl No
 ng\, PhD student in social psychology\, at&#160\;acc@iu.edu.&#160\;&#160\
 ;&#160\;&#160\;  &#160\;All Indiana University events\, groups\, activiti
 es\, and&#160\;educational\, cultural\, and historical observances welcom
 e all IU students and other members of the Indiana University community.F
 or more information\, view this event in BeInvolved (https://beinvolved.i
 ndiana.edu/event/11950465).
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p><span data-contrast="none">This is our la
 st book discussion meeting. What does it mean to be&#160\;an "other"? How
  can writing shift the boundaries between insider and outsider for both a
 uthor and audience? All are welcome to join the ACC in discussing these q
 uestions over pizza. We will discuss the last two essays of Viet Thanh Ng
 uyen's essay collection&#160\;</span><em><span data-contrast="none">To Sa
 ve and to Destroy: Writing as an Other</span></em><span data-contrast="no
 ne">. Digital copies of the eBook are&#160\;</span><a href="http://proxyi
 ub.uits.iu.edu/login?url=https://search.ebscohost.com/login.aspx?direct=t
 rue&amp\;scope=site&amp\;db=nlebk&amp\;db=nlabk&amp\;AN=4150320"><span da
 ta-contrast="none">freely available to access through IU Libraries</span>
