 llery&#160\;  Join us for a rare opportunity to explore the exhibition wi
 th Tasha Kimmet\, Curator of Asian Art.&#160\; This is a guided tour that
  starts at 3:30 p.m. If you miss the tour\, you're welcome to drop in to 
 explore the exhibition at your own pace until 5 p.m.&#160\;&#160\;4 - 5 p
 .m. | Reception | Martin Commons  After the tour\, drop by the Martin Com
 mons (2nd floor) for a light reception to celebrate this exhibition with 
 the Asian Culture Center and Asian Pacific American Faculty and Staff Cou
 ncil.About the Exhibition  Inspired by Indonesia's spectacular coral reef
 s\, acclaimed fiber artist Mulyana (b. 1984\, Bandung\, Indonesia) has cr
 eated an immersive\, handcrafted seascape where art and ecology meet. Exp
 lore colorful coral reefs\, playful fish\, and fantastical sea creatures 
 â€” all meticulously hand-knit and crocheted â€” while learning about how
  human wellness is interconnected with the wellbeing of our oceans.&#160\
 ;Acknowledgement  This program is hosted jointly by IU Asian Culture Cent
 er\, Asian Pacific American Faculty and Staff Council\, and the Eskenazi 
 Museum of Art.
